This paper focuses on improving Named Entity Recognition (NER) performance in chemical patents using deep learning techniques and pre-trained word embeddings. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of deep learning models and pre-trained embeddings suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also explores the impact of tokenizers on NER performance, which is relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of contextualized word embeddings suggests that it may also belong to the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
